🍳 Recipe Ideas App

A simple React application that helps users discover recipes based on ingredients they already have at home. Built as part of a take-home assignment for the Web Developer position at Aganitha.

👤 User Persona

Name: Taylor

Occupation: Busy Professional

Need: After work, Taylor wants to quickly decide what to cook based on ingredients available in the kitchen. The app provides easy recipe suggestions without the hassle of searching multiple sites.

🚀 Features

🔍 Ingredient-based Search → Enter any ingredient (e.g., chicken, rice) to discover related recipes.

📜 Recipe Suggestions → Displays meals with name, thumbnail, and quick access to details.

🍲 Detailed Recipe View → Shows ingredients with measurements, step-by-step instructions, and a YouTube cooking tutorial link (if available).

⚠️ Error Handling →

Empty input → friendly message.

No recipes found → clear feedback.

Network errors → user-friendly error display.

📱 Responsive UI → Works smoothly on desktop and mobile.

🔗 Live Demo

👉 https://rf6pv7.csb.app/

🛠️ Tech Stack

Frontend: React (TypeScript, Hooks, Functional Components)

Styling: Inline CSS for simplicity

API: TheMealDB

Endpoints used:

https://www.themealdb.com/api/json/v1/1/filter.php?i={ingredient} → Filter meals by ingredient.

https://www.themealdb.com/api/json/v1/1/lookup.php?i={id} → Get full meal details by ID.

